		<td><b>Re: Famicom stopped working - Recommendations?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If I remember correctly, the Famicom has a 1.5A picofuse that is often the source of this type of problem. I've seen it blown a few times when people bring theirs to me for repair; use a cheap multimeter in to check for continuity. It's the same fuse as in a SNES and they're easy to find online.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


