	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Famicom stopped working - Recommendations?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Some Famicom revisions absolutely have a 1.5A picofuse but not in your motherboard revision (yours is an older one, and the daughterboard is original), so there's one less thing to check. The best way to troubleshoot is to follow where the flow of power should be from component to component, and figure out where it stops. If everything seems okay, your problem is elsewhere.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


