		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />@OP, I did the same thing!<br />I recently got a Famicom console, and I knew not to use a NES power supply as it is AC.<br />For whatever reason I believed the SNES PSU to be DC, Maybe there's a Euro vs USA vs Japan difference? <br />So after doing an AV mod I plugged in the bare board to the SNES PSU. <br />After 2 seconds a cap (1000uf) near the power inlet popped and let out a puff of smoke.<br />I will be replacing that first, testing further, and obviously using a more suitable PSU.<br /><br />*EDIT* I have replaced the one cap, plugged in a Sega PSU and it's fine! <br />Good luck with yours.

		

